adjective.description: Of goods: subject to customs duty; dutiable.

origin: Late Middle English (in an earlier sense). From Anglo-Norman custumable, costumable, Anglo-Norman and Middle French coustumable dutiable, taxable, in accordance with custom, customary, accustomed to something, partly from costume, custume, coustume + -able, and partly from coustumer, custumer + -able.
